    Title: Phaedrus
    Locus: 256 E
By: Plato
Tags:
  - 902
Commentary: This can refer both to those who have reached the Primordial
  State in this life, and to those who are in the way of salvation after
  death.
---
Those who have once begun the heavenward pilgrimage may not go down again
to darkness and the journey beneath the earth, but they live in light always.
